.TH "reclaim_completed_tx" 9 "reclaim_completed_tx" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
reclaim_completed_tx \- reclaims completed TX Descriptors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" reclaim_completed_tx
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "struct sge_txq *q "  ","
.BI "int maxreclaim "  ","
.BI "bool unmap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "q" 12
the Tx queue to reclaim completed descriptors from
.IP "maxreclaim" 12
the maximum number of TX Descriptors to reclaim or -1
.IP "unmap" 12
whether the buffers should be unmapped for DMA

Reclaims Tx Descriptors that the SGE has indicated it has processed,
and frees the associated buffers if possible.  If \fImax\fP == -1, then
we'll use a defaiult maximum.  Called with the TX Queue locked.
